metadata.name: Bleak and White
metadata.description:
The world looks quite different when fog, snow and ice engulfs your surroundings.  I framed this image while standing in knee-deep snow near Abbe Creek, on a cold January morning.

What struck me was the pristine beauty and stillness of an otherwise bleak landscape, where the true shapes and essence of nature unfolded before me.  

Medium: Photography
Type: Digital
Size: 7360 x 4912 @ 300 dpi
